Below is a histogram between stock close price and date. At first, I wanted to utilize a lets_plot graph but could not determine how to fix the x_values saying 1.6T and 1.7T. The graph below is quite interesting, we can see that the overall market had downfalls in Spring 2020 and Spring 2022. According to Workday, the market is hot right now.

Below is a histogram between volume and date. Volume is a way of displaying market activity and liquidity. For instance, it seems as though Ford (F) has had concurrent bursts of volume thoughout the years. AT&T has also had reoccuring bursts of volume but not as dramatic as Ford.
